    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nN/A (Nvim API)\n\n### Feature description\n\nSometimes `nvim_get_mode()` doesn't return enough information to indicate the current mode, especially when in command-line mode (ref <https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/6127>, #11846), where `mode` returned by `nvim_get_mode()` sometimes doesn't start with `c`. A solution to this I can think of is to also return command-line type (`getcmdtype()`) from `nvim_get_mode()`. This will enable one to correctly tell whether the current mode is command-line mode from a fast API. However, introducing a new key to `nvim_get_mode()` will require modifying a lot of functional tests.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
