            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Is there a way to use getcmdtype() using the new vim.keymap.set? What I'm trying is to convert this:\r\n\r\n```vimscript\r\ncnoremap <expr> %% getcmdtype() == ':' ? expand('%:h') .. '/' : '%%'\r\n```\r\n\r\ninto lua using:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.keymap.set(\"c\", \"%%\", function()\r\n  return vim.fn.getcmdtype() == \":\" and vim.fn.expand('%:h'):append(\"/\") or \"%%\"\r\nend, { expr = true })\r\n```\r\nI get error about calling method 'append' (a nil value).\r\n\r\nI can't seem to get anything back from getcmdtype (or getcmdwintype, or getcmdline) other than an empty string. Is there a better way?",
